cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on deep learning for image classification, specifically on convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of backpropagation for learning the shape of the convolution, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new convolution unit, which can be considered as a new technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The use of the proposed unit for improving the performance of CNNs also falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on various datasets, which can be considered as a multimedia application (cs.MM - Multimedia).
